-------------------- Kubectl ----------------------------

There are two ways of making the things in k8s cluster either from command line or from the manifest file.

- kubectl apply -f namespace.yml (Apply namespace manifest file)
- kubectl apply -f pod.yml (Apply pod manifest file)

Some commands of kubectl :- 
1. kubectl create namespace nginx
2. kubectl delete namespace nginx

------------------------------------------------------

------------------- Deployment Manifest File --------------------
- Everything in K8s is a manifest file.

// Any pod that matches the label app nginx make it to 3 replicas.
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-deployment
  namespace: dev // -->> (all deployment or pods will be created in the same namespace).
  labels:
    app: nginx

spec: // --->> Deployment Specification
  replicas: 3 
  selector: // --->> Criteria
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  // nginx pod template below would be match on the basis of defined labels in selector criteria, this is optional either  
  // it could be made in new pod file or would be like this in the same file
  template: // --->> (Read as a Pod template, metadata labels would be match as per the criteria).
    metadata:
      name: nginx
      namespace: dev
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.14.2
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80

